						<summary>

						<p>On the wall at the left of entrance into the Jaina temple.</p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra, 1283 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 14th regnal year of the king, Subhānu, Bhādrapada śu. 15, (puṇṇami), corresponding to 1283 A.D., September 8.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the <hi rend="italic">Āchārya</hi> of Bhōgadēva. The inscription is damaged and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
